commitResults.messageBody:
Add Mockup of Bamboo Ui - Ui.png
Update README.md to be relevant to Bamboo

Let's refactor Name class to Description class 
to be more reflective of a "description" of an 
expense. 

A description is like an address and can take any
value - it just cannot be a whitespace.

This change includes updating fields in 
UI and tests.

Let's refactor Phone class to Amount class 
to be more reflective of a "amount" of an 
expense. 

Am amount comes in the format {dollars}.{cents}, 
although cents are optional.

This change includes updating fields in 
UI and tests.

TODO: decide if value of Amount should be stored
as dollars and cents instead (float accuracy).

Let's refactor Email class to Date class 
to be more reflective of a "date" of an 
expense. 

Use LocalDate instead of LocalDateTime to reflect date excluding hour and minutes.

This change includes updating fields in 
UI, tests, json files, class/methods,.

TODO: validation checks against future date input.

commitResults.messageBody: Update developer guide with writeup on proposed implementation of SortCommand

Add SortCommand, which sorts expenses in the
current view. 
SortCommand is able to sort by Amount, Description,
and Date - with the option of making a reversed sort.
SortCommand takes up to 3 parameters, sort is done 
according to priority of the parameter inputs
